# Lab 07: Inter-VLAN Routing (Router-on-a-Stick)

## Objective
Enable communication between VLANs using a router with subinterfaces.

## Topology
![Topology](topology.png)

## VLAN Design
- VLAN 10 (SALES)
- VLAN 20 (IT)

## IP Addressing
- VLAN 10 Gateway: 192.168.10.1
- VLAN 20 Gateway: 192.168.20.1

## Configuration Summary

### Switch
- VLANs created
- Access ports assigned
- Trunk port configured to router

### Router
- Subinterfaces created for each VLAN
- 802.1Q encapsulation configured
- IP addresses assigned

## Verification
- Inter-VLAN ping successful

## Lessons Learned
- Router-on-a-stick enables inter-VLAN routing
- Trunking allows multiple VLANs on one link

